parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission valve assembly can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
an unknown yellow warning light is illuminated
the vehicle is unable to accelerate above a certain speed (e.g.
40 mph)
the vehicle can only be driven at a low speed (e.g.
7 mph).

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Output Sensor and Transmission Control Module (TCM) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the output sensor and TCM can cause the vehicle to fail to accelerate properly, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to accelerate above a certain speed (e.g.
40 mph)
the vehicle is unable to accelerate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission vibration issue can cause discomfort and distraction to the driver and passengers, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates significantly at certain speeds (e.g.
40 mph
65 mph)
the vibration can be felt in the center console
armrest
steering wheel
and front seats
the vibration is more pronounced when driving uphill and in ECO mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission speed sensor can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop accelerating without warning, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle will stop accelerating without warning
then start moving again after an hour
the engine light will not illuminate during the incident
but will later indicate a problem with the transmission speed sensor
requiring replacement of the sensor and potentially the valve body.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or damage to property, especially if the vehicle surges forward without warning.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward without warning
crashes into objects
or experiences sudden unintended acceleration
often without any warning signs or illumination of the engine light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission valve body can cause the vehicle to experience sudden stops or loss of acceleration, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle will stop accelerating without warning
then start moving again after an hour
the engine light will not illuminate during the incident
but will later indicate a problem with the transmission speed sensor
requiring replacement of the sensor and potentially the valve body.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause injuries, obstruct the driver's vision, and lead to loss of control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents and potentially fatal consequences.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without warning
airbags deploy during normal driving conditions
airbags deploy without any prior warnings or lights
airbags deploy causing injuries
airbags deploy obstructing the driver's vision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Intelligent Key Not Detected error can cause the vehicle to decelerate unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control, and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries. Additionally, the error can prevent the vehicle from starting, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle displays an "Intelligent Key Not Detected" error message
the accelerator becomes unresponsive
the vehicle decelerates
the warning lights
infotainment center
and A/C remain operational
the vehicle will not start after power down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to continue turning in a full circle, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Abnormal sound while turning the steering wheel
the steering wheel continues to turn in a full circle
no warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering gearbox can cause the steering wheel to continue turning in a full circle, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Abnormal sound while turning the steering wheel
the steering wheel continues to turn in a full circle
no warning light is illuminated.
